result.execSummary:
The defendant Kelland Craig Nabors was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Knowingly Violate a Domestic Abuse Order - Injunction [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse Assessments], an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 813.12(8)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Kelland Craig Nabors in court with attorney Torrie R. Williams.  Defendant Kelland Craig Nabors in custody.  Nicolas J Heitman appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, and further advised that if not a United States citizen deportation is possible. Defendant examined as to plea, and entered a plea of guilty.  Court found defendant freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived all constitutional rights. Plea questionnaire waiver of rights and addendum to plea questionnaire received and filed. Parties stipulated to the criminal complaint as factual basis to sustain defendant's plea. Court found defendant guilty as charged and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered into the record.  
Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the state, defense and defendant.  State advised the Court they have complied with the Victims' Rights Law.  The Court ordered the Defendant to serve 90 days in the House of Correction, consecutive to any other sentence with credit for 0 days time served.  
Court orders all costs, assessments and surcharges, domestive vioence surcharge to be paid by 8-18-2017, failure to pay will result in civil judgment.  As this is a domestic violence conviction the defendant may never possess firearms or ammunition.
Defendant remanded.
Notice of Right to seek postconviction relief filed.
Plea date scheduled for 08-18-2015 at 01:30 pm.
Court ordered defendant to be produced for the next court date if still in custody.
